The paper deals with mean-payoff automata, which are commonly studied in the areas of logic (LO) and formal languages (FL). The paper also discusses the decidability and complexity of decision problems, which are typical topics in the area of data structures (DS). The paper also mentions nondeterministic and alternating mean-payoff automata, which are studied in the area of computational complexity (CC). Finally, the paper introduces a new class of quantitative languages, which involves the use of expressions, indicating a possible connection to programming languages (PL).
